<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Siegesmut, our group leader asked who wanted it for their main, if noone, then we random to group.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
It wasn't his call, it was Siegesmut's, he called NBG from the start, we had just been rolling everything prior because it wasn't an upgrade. The bracer was.<br>
<br>
Morgulm, I was selling RBB to purchase Spiked Seahorse, it's not like I was selling it to have more money. I was switching belts. Not that it's any of your business or anything.<br>
<br>
All you people who cry FFA because int casters don't get any loot, guess what? My alt is a wiz, a human wiz at that. At 207 int with extra 420 mana. It only cost me 20k to get there. 20k on a similarly equipped melee would fill 3-4 slots. However, this was not a FFA/NBG discussion. It was to let people know that a Stupid Bastard thought his opinion&gt;all. It was also to let people know that a chance to fix an error was ignored. <br>
<br>
I've won two books of ob in KC before when an caster needed because the group leader was a greedy melee. Both of them were given by me to the caster who both needed them most. With this being a NBG group set up by Siegesmut, then making an error on roll. I would expect to be given the bracer. It's what I would do, but I guess I'm a bit nicer than most. If you needed money, I told Juler I'd give him some for it so we both wouldn't get screwed. It was strange to see this person, which so many people say is nice, be anything but.<br>
<br>
